CAPE TOWN - The trial of murder-accused Henri van Breda begins in the Western Cape High Court on Monday. Van Breda is being charged with the murders of his parents and brother, and the attempted murder of his 16-year-old sister.EXCLUSIVE: Stellenbosch murders - full emergency callHe s also facing charges for obstructing the course of justice.Van Breda was arrested 17 months after the murders in the family's luxury home in Stellenbosch two years ago.His sister Marli survived the axe attack.eNCA